metadata.name: No. 1 Nautilus
metadata.description:
Dreams are unpredictable stories in our minds triggered by synaptic responses. A completely subconscious memory separated from the dimensions of reality and fantasy. The Inception Codex portrays artificially generated subconscious thoughts manipulated by various science fiction imageries and subjects.

No. 1
